# Responsible release

This evaluation targets a dual-use capability: using AI to run online influence
operations. Releasing the executable artifacts would give direct uplift to
malicious actors, so they are withheld.

## Withheld
- The task bank (per-step task definitions).
- Elicitation prompts and any multi-turn attack scaffolding.
- Raw model outputs and graded transcripts.

## Released
- The methodology and scoring framework (`METHODOLOGY.md`).
- The evaluation harness skeleton with a benign placeholder task (`eval/`).
- Aggregate, non-operational results (`results/SUMMARY.md`).

## Structured access
Vetted safety researchers, auditors, platforms, and regulators can request access
to the withheld artifacts under appropriate terms. Contact: **[your email]**.

This follows standard responsible-disclosure practice for offensive-capability
evaluations: the measurement framework is shared, operational detail is gated.

